The paper discusses the Multi-Agent Pathfinding (MAPF) problem, which is a well-known problem in the field of Artificial Intelligence (AI) and Robotics (RO). The paper also mentions applications of MAPF in automated warehouses and autonomous vehicles, which are relevant to the sub-category of Multi-Agent Systems (MA). The paper proposes a new grid-based benchmark for MAPF, which is related to the sub-category of Planning and Scheduling (PL). Finally, the paper discusses different assumptions and objectives in MAPF, which are relevant to the sub-category of Systems and Control (SY). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.MA, cs.SY, and cs.PL.
